item.title: CVE-2018-4010|2024-09-16T17:54:36.228Z -- talos -- protonvpn
item.description: An exploitable code execution vulnerability exists in the connect functionality of ProtonVPN VPN client 1.5.1. A specially crafted configuration file can cause a privilege escalation, resulting in the ability to execute arbitrary commands with the system's privileges.
